\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Student Needs and Expectations\
\
## Core Motivations\
Students choose universities based on:\
- Career outcomes and employability\
- International recognition of degrees\
- Practical, hands-on learning\
- Opportunities for internships and networking\
\
## International Student Needs\
- Clear visa and relocation guidance\
- English-language instruction\
- Cultural integration support\
- Career opportunities in the local market (Germany/EU)\
\
## Academic Expectations\
- Industry-relevant curriculum\
- Real-world projects and case studies\
- Access to experienced faculty with professional backgrounds\
- Flexible learning formats (hybrid, practical workshops)\
\
## Emotional Drivers\
- Desire for personal growth and independence\
- Confidence in future career prospects\
- Belonging to an international community\
- Living in a dynamic, modern city\
\
## Pain Points\
- Uncertainty about job prospects after graduation\
- Complex application and visa processes\
- Lack of clarity about program value\
- Overwhelming number of study options\
\
## Content Preferences\
Students respond well to:\
- Clear, practical advice\
- Career-focused content\
- Real student stories and testimonials\
- Step-by-step guides (e.g., \'93How to study in Berlin\'94)\
\
## Decision Factors\
- Reputation of the institution\
- Location (city attractiveness)\
- Tuition fees vs. ROI\
- Alumni success stories}